Title: The Last Signal
Author: Genlock
Draft date: 2026-07-16

# ACT ONE

INT. LIGHTHOUSE - NIGHT

= Harlan decodes the pattern and it answers back.

Harlan Morse hunches over the logbook, scrawling coordinates by candlelight. The radio crackles behind him, a five-beat rhythm buried in the static, and every time he matches an entry the rhythm tightens, as if the noise itself were leaning closer to check his work against its own.

HARLAN (V.O.)
Thirty-one years I logged the sea. Turns out the sea was logging me.

[[Note: hold the V.O. until the second pass of the beam.]]

The beam sweeps the room. Papers lift. The rhythm stops.

HARLAN
(quietly)
Say it again.

CUT TO:

EXT. CLIFF EDGE - CONTINUOUS

/*
Deleted beat: Eli's boat visible offshore.
Keep for the S01E02 recap maybe.
*/

Harlan stands at the rail with the logbook against his chest, fog rolling up the cliff face.

ELI (O.S.)
You left the light off that night. Say that part.

INT. LIGHTHOUSE BASEMENT - MOMENTS LATER

The hatch stands open. The five-beat rhythm rises from below, patient as a metronome.
